Day 87 – Road to Fluent Spanish Summary
Today focused on Duolingo, Memrise, weekly conversational phrases, and Pimsleur Unit 3 Lesson 7. This lesson introduced more difficult past-tense and travel-related phrases, especially around files, hotel reservations, credit cards, and talking about what someone has or has not done.

Duolingo / Memrise Review
New and reviewed phrases included:

El camarero tiene razón = The waiter is right.
El pescado aquí es delicioso = The fish here is delicious.
Se ve delicioso = It looks delicious.
Su vino especial = Your special wine.
Mi hija quiere ser una estrella pop = My daughter wants to be a pop star.
Quiere viajar por el mundo = He wants to travel the world.
Convertirse en = to become.
Rico = rich.
Pobre = poor.
Todo mi vida he querido convertirme en un escritor famoso = My whole life I have wanted to become a famous writer.
